 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udthamilaye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dthamilaye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 8:09:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22859.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Suggestion</span><hr size=1> Mrmann.<br>
<br>
Lets take this from pure melee perspective:<br>
<br>
Lets imagine that at this point in EQ, there would be NO haste items of any kind. There also would be NO enchanter haste spells or bard haste songs. You would have gone up to 60 or whatever without ANY kind of haste.<br>
<br>
Then your neighbourhood mage could suddenly summon an item which has 10% (15%?) percent haste. He could ALSO summon an item that raised the damage of any weapon you use by 2. He could summon an item that lowered the aggro of every hit you do with any weapon. Another summoned item would raise your chances to get bigger backstabs. 5th item would lower your chance to get stunned when something hits you. All these items could be worn at the same time. <br>
<br>
Casters are now in that situation.<br>
<br>
*********<br>
Dthamilaye K'Tang, 57th mage &lt;Tide&gt; (Tunare) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udthamilaye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dthamilaye</A> at: 3/18/02 8:14:22 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umysthyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mysthyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 8:50:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22859.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> you forgot</span><hr size=1> You forgot the part about not gaining any noticeable damage from items for the past 3 years so that a yak (8/24), trident of the seven seas (11/30), and cristalline spears (13/30) are about where you're damage is at lvl 50. <br>
<br>
Focus items promise to be to casters what weapons and haste items are to melee, a way to boost their power and effectiveness in a way that’s been lacking since release. Seams like the easiest way to get focus items at first will be mag summons so they will have the most direct access to them. <br>
<br>
This is a very valid topic for a rogue board imo. If you remember back to pre-kunak mag and rogue were almost synonymous in a group. If you wanted good damage you could invite either one. Now these present focus items won’t put mages on par with rogue damage the way they should be but the better drop ones might. Rogues might find their unjust position as the ultimate damage dealer challenged at last.<br>
<br>
Mysthyl Endowyn<br>
Sorcerer of Drinal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uferessa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Feressa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 9:11:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22859.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: you forgot</span><hr size=1> I very much doubt that Verant has tested these properly, and they've always had problems with getting caster balance right anyway. No-one in their right mind is going to pretend it's hard to level up to 50: Kunark made that process pretty easy. Does Verant really think that making the low levels a cake-walk is going to boost their subscriber base?<br>
<br>
Mages have certainly needed a boost, but do they need that starting at level 4? I don't think so.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umysthyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mysthyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/18/02 9:30:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22859.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> lvl 4 too early?</span><hr size=1> Actually Feressa I would argue that lvl 4 isn’t soon enough. You say leveling to 50 has gotten too easy already and I would agree with you there, for some classes. It’s a sad fact that magicians like all offensive casters haven’t benefited directly from this. A magician from 1 to 50 is almost exactly the same as they were pre kunark when it comes to ability to do damage (primary role). Spell efficiency is the same, med rates are the same, pet damage is the same. Since magicians, and other offensive casters, don’t gain offensive power through items they have been largely left behind in the enormous power increase we’ve seen pre 50. Sure they can benefit indirectly through the wider variety of leveling zones now available or by grouping with a melee type but that is no reason why they shouldn’t also increase in power to match tanks. <br>
<br>
A lvl 20 rogue NOT TWINKED can go out and spend pocket change for a weapon that is better then level 50s use to use. There is no denying the huge effect increasingly better equipment and the trickle down effect has had on the game and its nice to see casters might soon be benefiting from it too with focus items.<br>
<br>
Mysthyl Endowyn<br>
